619:  * subquery_planner
620:  *	  Invokes the planner on a subquery.  We recurse to here for each
621:  *	  sub-SELECT found in the query tree.
622:  *
623:  * glob is the global state for the current planner run.
624:  * parse is the querytree produced by the parser & rewriter.
625:  * parent_root is the immediate parent Query's info (NULL at the top level).
626:  * hasRecursion is true if this is a recursive WITH query.
627:  * tuple_fraction is the fraction of tuples we expect will be retrieved.
628:  * tuple_fraction is interpreted as explained for grouping_planner, below.
629:  * setops is used for set operation subqueries to provide the subquery with
630:  * the context in which it's being used so that Paths correctly sorted for the
631:  * set operation can be generated.  NULL when not planning a set operation
632:  * child, or when a child of a set op that isn't interested in sorted input.
633:  *
634:  * Basically, this routine does the stuff that should only be done once
635:  * per Query object.  It then calls grouping_planner.  At one time,
636:  * grouping_planner could be invoked recursively on the same Query object;
637:  * that's not currently true, but we keep the separation between the two
638:  * routines anyway, in case we need it again someday.
639:  *
640:  * subquery_planner will be called recursively to handle sub-Query nodes
641:  * found within the query's expressions and rangetable.
642:  *
643:  * Returns the PlannerInfo struct ("root") that contains all data generated
644:  * while planning the subquery.  In particular, the Path(s) attached to
645:  * the (UPPERREL_FINAL, NULL) upperrel represent our conclusions about the
646:  * cheapest way(s) to implement the query.  The top level will select the
647:  * best Path and pass it through createplan.c to produce a finished Plan.
648:  *--------------------
649:  */
650: PlannerInfo *
651: subquery_planner(PlannerGlobal *glob, Query *parse, PlannerInfo *parent_root,
652: 				 bool hasRecursion, double tuple_fraction,
653: 				 SetOperationStmt *setops)
